snippets.title: bigtable createInstance Sample
snippets.description: Create an instance within a project. Note that exactly one of Cluster.serve_nodes and Cluster.cluster_config.cluster_autoscaling_config can be set. If serve_nodes is set to non-zero, then the cluster is manually scaled. If cluster_config.cluster_autoscaling_config is non-empty, then autoscaling is enabled.

snippets.title: bigtable getInstance Sample
snippets.description: Gets information about an instance.

snippets.title: bigtable listInstances Sample
snippets.description: Lists information about instances in a project.

snippets.title: bigtable updateInstance Sample
snippets.description: Updates an instance within a project. This method updates only the display name and type for an Instance. To update other Instance properties, such as labels, use PartialUpdateInstance.

snippets.title: bigtable partialUpdateInstance Sample
snippets.description: Partially updates an instance within a project. This method can modify all fields of an Instance and is the preferred way to update an Instance.

snippets.title: bigtable deleteInstance Sample
snippets.description: Delete an instance from a project.

snippets.title: bigtable createCluster Sample
snippets.description: Creates a cluster within an instance. Note that exactly one of Cluster.serve_nodes and Cluster.cluster_config.cluster_autoscaling_config can be set. If serve_nodes is set to non-zero, then the cluster is manually scaled. If cluster_config.cluster_autoscaling_config is non-empty, then autoscaling is enabled.

snippets.title: bigtable getCluster Sample
snippets.description: Gets information about a cluster.

snippets.title: bigtable listClusters Sample
snippets.description: Lists information about clusters in an instance.

snippets.title: bigtable updateCluster Sample
snippets.description: Updates a cluster within an instance. Note that UpdateCluster does not support updating cluster_config.cluster_autoscaling_config. In order to update it, you must use PartialUpdateCluster.

snippets.title: bigtable partialUpdateCluster Sample
snippets.description: Partially updates a cluster within a project. This method is the preferred way to update a Cluster. To enable and update autoscaling, set cluster_config.cluster_autoscaling_config. When autoscaling is enabled, serve_nodes is treated as an OUTPUT_ONLY field, meaning that updates to it are ignored. Note that an update cannot simultaneously set serve_nodes to non-zero and cluster_config.cluster_autoscaling_config to non-empty, and also specify both in the update_mask. To disable autoscaling, clear cluster_config.cluster_autoscaling_config, and explicitly set a serve_node count via the update_mask.

snippets.title: bigtable deleteCluster Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a cluster from an instance.

snippets.title: bigtable createAppProfile Sample
snippets.description: Creates an app profile within an instance.

snippets.title: bigtable getAppProfile Sample
snippets.description: Gets information about an app profile.

snippets.title: bigtable listAppProfiles Sample
snippets.description: Lists information about app profiles in an instance.

snippets.title: bigtable updateAppProfile Sample
snippets.description: Updates an app profile within an instance.

snippets.title: bigtable deleteAppProfile Sample
snippets.description: Deletes an app profile from an instance.

snippets.title: bigtable getIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Gets the access control policy for an instance resource. Returns an empty policy if an instance exists but does not have a policy set.

snippets.title: bigtable setIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Sets the access control policy on an instance resource. Replaces any existing policy.

snippets.title: bigtable testIamPermissions Sample
snippets.description: Returns permissions that the caller has on the specified instance resource.

snippets.title: bigtable listHotTablets Sample
snippets.description: Lists hot tablets in a cluster, within the time range provided. Hot tablets are ordered based on CPU usage.

snippets.title: bigtable createTable Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new table in the specified instance. The table can be created with a full set of initial column families, specified in the request.

snippets.title: bigtable createTableFromSnapshot Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new table from the specified snapshot. The target table must not exist. The snapshot and the table must be in the same instance. Note: This is a private alpha release of Cloud Bigtable snapshots. This feature is not currently available to most Cloud Bigtable customers. This feature might be changed in backward-incompatible ways and is not recommended for production use. It is not subject to any SLA or deprecation policy.

snippets.title: bigtable listTables Sample
snippets.description: Lists all tables served from a specified instance.

snippets.title: bigtable getTable Sample
snippets.description: Gets metadata information about the specified table.

snippets.title: bigtable updateTable Sample
snippets.description: Updates a specified table.

snippets.title: bigtable deleteTable Sample
snippets.description: Permanently deletes a specified table and all of its data.

snippets.title: bigtable undeleteTable Sample
snippets.description: Restores a specified table which was accidentally deleted.

snippets.title: bigtable modifyColumnFamilies Sample
snippets.description: Performs a series of column family modifications on the specified table. Either all or none of the modifications will occur before this method returns, but data requests received prior to that point may see a table where only some modifications have taken effect.

snippets.title: bigtable dropRowRange Sample
snippets.description: Permanently drop/delete a row range from a specified table. The request can specify whether to delete all rows in a table, or only those that match a particular prefix.

snippets.title: bigtable generateConsistencyToken Sample
snippets.description: Generates a consistency token for a Table, which can be used in CheckConsistency to check whether mutations to the table that finished before this call started have been replicated. The tokens will be available for 90 days.

snippets.title: bigtable checkConsistency Sample
snippets.description: Checks replication consistency based on a consistency token, that is, if replication has caught up based on the conditions specified in the token and the check request.

snippets.title: bigtable snapshotTable Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new snapshot in the specified cluster from the specified source table. The cluster and the table must be in the same instance. Note: This is a private alpha release of Cloud Bigtable snapshots. This feature is not currently available to most Cloud Bigtable customers. This feature might be changed in backward-incompatible ways and is not recommended for production use. It is not subject to any SLA or deprecation policy.

snippets.title: bigtable getSnapshot Sample
snippets.description: Gets metadata information about the specified snapshot. Note: This is a private alpha release of Cloud Bigtable snapshots. This feature is not currently available to most Cloud Bigtable customers. This feature might be changed in backward-incompatible ways and is not recommended for production use. It is not subject to any SLA or deprecation policy.

snippets.title: bigtable listSnapshots Sample
snippets.description: Lists all snapshots associated with the specified cluster. Note: This is a private alpha release of Cloud Bigtable snapshots. This feature is not currently available to most Cloud Bigtable customers. This feature might be changed in backward-incompatible ways and is not recommended for production use. It is not subject to any SLA or deprecation policy.

snippets.title: bigtable deleteSnapshot Sample
snippets.description: Permanently deletes the specified snapshot. Note: This is a private alpha release of Cloud Bigtable snapshots. This feature is not currently available to most Cloud Bigtable customers. This feature might be changed in backward-incompatible ways and is not recommended for production use. It is not subject to any SLA or deprecation policy.

snippets.title: bigtable createBackup Sample
snippets.description: Starts creating a new Cloud Bigtable Backup.  The returned backup [long-running operation][google.longrunning.Operation] can be used to track creation of the backup. The [metadata][google.longrunning.Operation.metadata] field type is [CreateBackupMetadata][google.bigtable.admin.v2.CreateBackupMetadata]. The [response][google.longrunning.Operation.response] field type is [Backup][google.bigtable.admin.v2.Backup], if successful. Cancelling the returned operation will stop the creation and delete the backup.

snippets.title: bigtable getBackup Sample
snippets.description: Gets metadata on a pending or completed Cloud Bigtable Backup.

snippets.title: bigtable updateBackup Sample
snippets.description: Updates a pending or completed Cloud Bigtable Backup.

snippets.title: bigtable deleteBackup Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a pending or completed Cloud Bigtable backup.

snippets.title: bigtable listBackups Sample
snippets.description: Lists Cloud Bigtable backups. Returns both completed and pending backups.

snippets.title: bigtable restoreTable Sample
snippets.description: Create a new table by restoring from a completed backup. The new table must be in the same project as the instance containing the backup.  The returned table [long-running operation][google.longrunning.Operation] can be used to track the progress of the operation, and to cancel it.  The [metadata][google.longrunning.Operation.metadata] field type is [RestoreTableMetadata][google.bigtable.admin.RestoreTableMetadata].  The [response][google.longrunning.Operation.response] type is [Table][google.bigtable.admin.v2.Table], if successful.

snippets.title: bigtable getIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Gets the access control policy for a Table or Backup resource. Returns an empty policy if the resource exists but does not have a policy set.

snippets.title: bigtable setIamPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Sets the access control policy on a Table or Backup resource. Replaces any existing policy.

snippets.title: bigtable testIamPermissions Sample
snippets.description: Returns permissions that the caller has on the specified Table or Backup resource.
